Check if you are washing your hands well.
We all know that you need to wash them (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds to wash enough to remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands.
And most of us do it less.
It is enough warm water and ordinary soap - it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
When washing, we rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hands, but also: the tips of the fingers (jointed or single) - rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, the spaces between the fingers (interlace the hands, rubbing the fingers against each other), thumbs - we cover each thumb with the other hand and in such a hug we turn it for a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when you can not wash your hands), you should wipe your hands with a wet handkerchief, and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from PLN 5).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the door handles or doors with your washed hands (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it through a paper towel.
Iranian President Says He Rejected U.S. Talks Proposal, Donald Trump Denies
Tehran did not hold talks with the U.S. at the U.N. General Assembly in New York, despite the U.S. offer to lift sanctions, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on Friday.
US President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the lifting of the restrictions, which he did not agree to.
Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said the United States had proposed lifting all sanctions against Tehran in exchange for negotiating a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran’s nuclear program and its ballistic missile program.
Rouhani: Iran will not hold talks in an atmosphere of maximum pressure
Iran’s president said he had not agreed to hold the talks because of the “toxic atmosphere.”
He said he had met with American diplomats because he had succumbed to the pressures of France, Germany and Britain.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in an atmosphere of “maximum pressure”.
“Even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in the 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be,” Rouhani said.
A day earlier, the Iranian leader said that he did not rule out talks with the US, and accused the European parties of favoring US sanctions on Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran after the US withdrawal from the nuclear agreement “are a prerequisite that does not allow” to establish dialogue.
“If we can lift this precondition and if America can lift sanctions and the maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America,” he said.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with US President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation last week at the UN General Assembly.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no”
Donald Trump tweeted that he had rejected the Iranian side’s request.
“Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said no!” the US president tweeted.
Tension with atomic agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease tensions between Washington and Tehran in order to somehow save the 2015 deal with Iran, of which they were signatories.
In exchange for the lifting of economic sanctions, Iran would abandon its nuclear weapons program and put the nuclear sector under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the United States from the agreement in May 2015, the other signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
So far, nothing's come of it.
Washington is using the tactic of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and the sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has said that if it does not receive a permit to export the raw material, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
