The power of jumps.
The title of the coverage of amateur sports competitions, played on Sunday afternoon 15 September at the hippodrome at Oleandry Street in Oława, may be confusing for some.
The road to true power is a long one, but this is what one of the types of horse rivalry is called.
The jumping competition consists in overcoming higher and higher obstacles by the rider and horse, which in the most prestigious international competitions exceed even two meters.
It is worth noting that the long-standing and still unbeaten world record, set in 1949 by Chilean Albert Larraguibel, on a “Huaso” horse, is 247 cm.
Nobody jumped that high in Oława, of course, but the result of the best local amazon at the level of 135 cm is also not the worst...
The competition organized by the tireless Jan Sienkiewicz and other JKS activists “In the saddle” was a demonstration part of the “Rainbow Equestrian Competitions” played there a little earlier, which we write about in this issue of the newspaper, on page 22.
The competition was joined by eight amazons, who trained riding in JKS in Olawa.
Four of them competed on ponies and four on big horses.
The first group was best managed by Nikola Szołdra, who was riding a crazy “Sprinter”.
This small but dynamic steed started with overcoming obstacles spread at a height of 40 cm, and ended only at the station with the upper beam 125 cm away from the ground.
However, he did not give up easily and only after three more refusals was the jury of the competition removed from further competition.
The second place in pony jumping was taken by Amelia Pawlak, who was riding “Famy”, and the third place was taken by Lena Borun on “Harmider”.
Ambitiously fought the youngest participant of the tournament - Inga Aksman, galloping and jumping over obstacles on a small mare "Carmen".
Even greater emotions accompanied the amazon contestants and spectators during the competition with the participation of large horses.
The menacing falls included Paulina Szewczyk, who was riding the “Declaration” and Anastasia Abramenko, who was riding the “Flight”.
Fortunately, apart from minor bruises, nothing bad happened to the amazon or the horses, so they continued to participate in the competition.
Weronika Łuczkiewicz had a lot of problems with introducing the young mare “Wineta” to the show jumping.
We needed either a trainer’s assistance or another horse for the couple, followed by a little crazy “Vineta”.
After passing the obstacle from the showjumping, she also rode full gallop, so sometimes in the boxes and in the expansion room it was dangerous. “Everything is under control!”, calmed Jan Sienkiewicz a little bit with this frightened viewers, especially the youngest ones.
From the beginning of the competition of large horses, Marta Masalska, riding a beautifully presented "Whisky" performed great on the show.
This dignified mare, paired with an experienced amazon, was the first to jump 135 cm after the second approach in the final stage and it was the best result of the competition at that moment.
After a while, however, Paulina Szewczyk on the “Declaration”, Weronika Łuczkiewicz on the “Vinet” and Anastasia Abramenko on the “Flight”.
For the decoration of the fleet and to receive prizes in the form of equestrian equipment, all these athletes went together, and in the end, together with the amazon ponies in the rhythm of Radecki's march, they made an impressive honorary round, ending with this interesting and emotional competition.
