Max Kolonko cuts himself off from KWW The Patriotic Revolution of Max Kolonko
KWW The Patriotic Revolution of Max Kolonko is the name of the election committee under which the political formation #R Revolution of Mariusz Max Kolonko was to go to the October parliamentary elections.
The revolution directed its proposal especially to young voters with right-wing views.
Before the elections, Kolonko announced cooperation with Marek Jakubiak or Paweł Kukiz, but none of these coalitions took place, and KWW Patriotic Revolution itself did not even manage to collect enough signatures to issue letters in any electoral district in Poland.
Now Kolonko has announced on Twitter that he has ended his cooperation with KWW Patriotic Revolution of Max Kolonko.
"I will be waiting for the above mentioned KWW to delete my name from the name.
I kindly ask you not to associate my person with the aforementioned entity," he added and announced that more information will be provided soon.
It is not yet known whether the journalist will continue his activities or whether this is the end of the #R Revolution formation.
On July 4, American Independence Day, journalist Mariusz Max Kolonko announced the creation of a new political formation - #R Revolution.
In recent years, Kolonko has become famous for running the Max TV channel on YouTube, where he comments on events in Poland and around the world.
“We’ve had enough of politicians, we’ve had enough of your stupid games, we’ve had enough of your amateur governments.
It is time for the authorities in the state to take over the nation and rule for the good of the nation," Kolonko said at the time.
The party’s agenda includes issues related to the judiciary (it should be elected in general elections), tax changes (equalization of the tax-free amount for all), war reparations (in the form of military assistance to the countries of NATO’s eastern flank, with particular emphasis on Poland), holding a referendum on the possession of weapons, limiting the number of deputies or introducing single-member constituencies.
A few days after the announcement of the new political formation Mariusz Max Kolonko started talks with Marek Jakubiak.
At the end of July, Kolonko posted on his social media profile information suggesting that #R will join forces with the Kukiz'15 movement.
However, none of these coalitions ultimately took place.
UBS: Gold close to the equilibrium point
“The euro exchange rate will remain close to the PLN 4.35 ceiling in the coming months, which will be accompanied by a weak situation on global markets,” announces Michael Bolliger from UBS Wealth Management.
“Expectations of maintaining a solid pace of economic growth and stable monetary policy support the stabilisation of the zloty’s quotations at the current level,” the specialist said in an interview with Bankier.pl.
In his opinion, despite the clear inflationary pressure, the Monetary Policy Council will not decide to raise rates in an environment in which the vast majority of central banks are easing policy.
"While the zloty is properly valued - the euro quotations should remain in the coming months around the ceiling of 4.35 PLN - the Polish bonds are not very attractive.
Much more favorable yields than Polish securities are offered by bonds from emerging markets”, says Michael Bolliger, Head of Asset Allocation to Emerging Markets, UBS Wealth Management.
According to the specialist, the main threat to the Polish economy is the deterioration of the global economic situation.
“The global slowdown may be even worse, but it should not lead to a severe recession, or at the most, to GDP dynamics falling slightly below zero,” announced Michael Bolliger.
“Investors should be underestimating global actions that may be harmed by the lack of prospects for resolving the US-China trade conflict and other geopolitical risk factors, including Donald Trump’s impeachment procedure and Brexit.
Among the stock markets, Europe should behave relatively the least”, according to the latest letter to investors by the main manager of UBS Wealth Management, Mark Haefele.
Shares from eurozone countries should behave worse than the US ones, because they are more vulnerable in conditions of increased uncertainty around global trade and fears of a slowdown.
According to Michael Bolliger, after the bull market in the bond markets of the safest countries pushed the German 10-year yields to minus 0.74 percent, it is still possible to deepen the decline in profitability.
However, in the long term, the profitability of long-term bonds should no longer fall, but only short-term ones, due to the easing of banks’ monetary policy.
The Fed has the largest scope for rate cuts, which should lead to a weakening of the US currency in the coming years.
The long-term equilibrium point for the euro is the USD 1.29, which would mean a 19% potential strengthening of the single currency to the dollar.
We expect further cuts in the Fed’s rates, which will result in a decrease in the global monetary policy gap.
“The dollar’s strength in the long run may not be sustained by current account and budget deficits,” Bolliger said.
