Confidential Report of the German Ministry of Defence
Since the beginning of 2014, the Bundeswehr has reported the disappearance of 39 weapons, 39 parts of weapons and 19,445 rounds of ammunition, according to a confidential report prepared by the German Ministry of Defense.
This was reported by the media group RedaktionsNetzwerk Deutschland (RND).
According to a document from the parliamentary office of the Secretary of State in the Ministry of Defense Peter Tauber (CDU), two pieces of weapons, one part of weapons and 3,474 pieces of ammunition have been retraced so far.
Among the military equipment still missing are six MG3 universal machine guns, 11 G3 automatic rifles, four G36 automatic rifles, six signal guns, and two P8 pistols.
In addition, 30 barrels for MG3 machine guns are missing.
Martina Renner, vice-president of the Left Party, expressed her concern about the situation.
She told RND reporters that the number of weapons and ammunition missing was "disturbing".
As a result of the investigations, only a small part of the lost equipment was found.
Martina Renner summed up the effects of these actions as a "poor balance sheet".
She also criticized the fact that the list does not show whether there is also a weapon that was found during the investigation against Bundeswehr lieutenant Franco A. In December 2017, the federal prosecutor’s office in Karlsruhe accused him of preparing a serious act of violence threatening the security of the state and violating the provisions of the law regulating access to firearms.
The officer was accused of preparing attacks on leading German politicians for far-right and racist reasons.
His “blacklist” of targets, which fell into the hands of the prosecutor’s office, included the then Minister of Justice Heiko Maas from the SPD, Claudia Roth from the Green party and Anetta Kahane, a human rights defender and founder of the Amadeu Antonio Stiftung foundation in Berlin.
Franco A. illegally acquired four firearms, more than 1,000 rounds of ammunition, and more than 50 explosives.
