Senate Decides on Key Laws
The Senate adopted without amendments the Act on the Disclosure of Family Assets of the Most Important State Officials and on Flights of the Most Important Persons in the State.
52 senators voted for the amendment to the law on the family property of state officials, 14 voted against, three abstained.
Thus, the senators decided to reject 12 amendments tabled by Senator Sławomir Rybicki during the Wednesday debate.
According to him, the amendments were to “civilize” the law and limit the scope of the information provided in the statement on the financial situation of own children, children of the spouse, children prepared for cases in which children remain in a common household with a person obliged to make a statement.
The Act on the Publicity of the Family of the Most Important State Officials, the draft of which was created in the Prime Minister’s office, was passed by the Sejm on 11 September.
The regulations stipulate that, among others, the Prime Minister, ministers, deputies, MEPs, senators, presidents of the Constitutional Court, the Supreme Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as those who are at the head of other state institutions, will be obliged to include information about the personal property of spouses, children and people living together in a financial statement.
The Senate also did not propose amendments to the law on flights of the most important people in the state.
It regulates which flights have HEAD status and who can be on board government aircraft along with the most important people in the state.
The law also specifies who is responsible for maintaining the Central Register of Flights.
55 senators voted in favour of the bill, 12 against and four abstentions.
According to the law, every flight of the president will be a flight “performed in an official mission”.
The President will be accompanied by family members and other persons invited by the President.
On the other hand, the flight in the official mission of the Prime Minister and the Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate will be only a flight “taken for the purpose of performing tasks directly related to the function performed”.
The law also clarifies the list of people who can accompany the most important people in the country during the flight.
